    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-06-21T23:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-06-21T23:00:00-05:00" n="155"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d155">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/12297: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Germany</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morris</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-06-22T06:00:00+02:00"
                            >June 22, 1941—6 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received June 22—5:37 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2484. At 5:30 this morning, German summer time, Goebbels,<note n="87"
                        xml:id="d155fn87">Josef Goebbels, Reich Minister of Propaganda.</note> read
                    on the radio a proclamation of the Reich Chancellor to the German people
                    outlining the course of German-Russian relations since the beginning of the war
                    and announcing the inauguration of military action against Russia on the entire
                    front from the Arctic Ocean to the Black Sea.<note n="88" xml:id="d155fn88">For
                        text of the German statement, see the <hi rend="italic">New York Times</hi>,
                        June 22, 1941, p. 1.</note> It was stated that the armed force of Finland
                    and Rumania would participate in the German effort.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Morris</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
